{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}]},{"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}]},{"level":2,"text":"Sharing state","anchor":"Sharing-state","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will require that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SignUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, if you want any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and specify a URL:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"key:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Similar to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"type":"text","text":", upon launch of the application the initial"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the application will automatically update."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" article"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for more detailed information."}]}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchite